> â“ â€œFor each microservice do we have load balancer (Ribbon)?â€

âœ… Yes, every **client microservice** that makes calls to others has its own Ribbon logic.

> â“ â€œIs it once consumed part, does it send to others?â€

âŒ No. The response from Service B goes **directly back** to Service A. Ribbon doesnâ€™t act as a proxy or intermediate forwarder. It just **chooses an instance** to call.

> â“ â€œIn EKS, is this taken care of?â€

âœ… Yes! In EKS:
- Kubernetes DNS + kube-proxy handles discovery and routing.
- You donâ€™t need Ribbon or Eureka.
- Calls are made to stable DNS names and automatically routed to healthy pods.

